    "FA, with its fine-grained, spherical particles ranging from 1 to 100 µm, enhances workability and lowers water demand in concrete.",
    "Slag has granular, glassy particles with rough edges and angular shapes between 10 and 150 µm, offering moderate reactivity and good durability.",
    "Volcanic ash, with a broad particle size distribution from 0.1 to 500 µm, has highly irregular particles that influence its ability to react and its use in various concrete applications.",
    "GGBFS has consistently shaped particles with a dense structure and smooth surfaces, sized from 1 to 100 µm, which contribute to increased strength and durability due to their uniformity.",
